You need the following libraries:

 -GTK2
 -libpng
 -libz

You also need Python for one step of the compile process.

Optional: Get the gfract-palettes-??.tar.gz file from the same place you
got this program from and unpack it to your chosen location.

Then:

-make
-strip gfract (optional)
-cp gfract /usr/local/bin (or where-ever)
-cp gfract.xpm /where/you/keep/your/pixmaps (optional)

Optional: The supplied gfract.xpm works an icon for the program.

Read KEYS for information on keyboard shortcuts.
